"n.(伤口的)缝线；v.缝合 【英】 n.(伤口的)缝线(a strand or fiber used to sew parts of the living body);v.缝合(to unite, close, or secure with sutures) 【考】 反义词：incision(切 开) 【记】 sut(=sen 缝)+ure 【例】 suture a wound n. (伤口的)缝线; 缝合处; v 缝合 【记】读: 速车, 被速度很快的车撞上了, 赶快到医院缝合伤口. 【反】incision(n 切割; 切口); avulse(v 把...撕脱) 【记】源自sew + ture；sew + 音：扯，将扯开的sew上；音：绣扯，袖扯，袖子扯掉了用针绣缝起来 【相关】stitch 缝, 缝合 suture (n.)  early 15c., ""surgical stitching of a wound, etc.,"" from Latin sutura ""a seam, a sewing together,"" from sutus, past participle of suere ""to sew"" (see sew). Meaning ""a seam, a line of joining or closure"" is from 1570s. suture (v.)  1777, from suture (n.). Related: Sutured; suturing."
